SOURCE: Media Institute of Southern Africa, 16 Dec. 2008
NOTES: Journalist with ZBC abducted and beaten by unknown men.
Toposa bandit shot by police reservist in response to village raid (in which 7 civilians were killed and 88 animals stolen).
Student rioters attack journalists with fists and stones and vandalise the journalists equipment and vehicles.

"Three vehicles were damaged when Inkwanca ANC branches clashed in Sterkstroom on Sunday." Inkwanca has four branches, two in Molteno and two in Sterkstroom, which are embroiled in a contest to have their municipality played under Section 139 administration.

Arrest:Sixty young men were arrested by Imbonerakure between August 18 and 19 in Kayogoro capital, and taken to the municipal police station. Local sources said the group was sent down from the buses leaving for Tanzania where they claim to work in tobacco plantations.
Malian troops committed human rights abuses on Tuareg civilians in Douentza.
LRA rebels attacked a Kitgum suburb - 4 civilians were killed
Gunmen lobbed four hand grenades into Bakara market. Two civilians were killed.

ASSOC_ACTOR_1: Civilian JTF: Civilian Joint Task Force
NOTES: Accompanied by the "Civilian JTF", military forces raid Boko Haram locations at Mogole, Ngaiwa, Tongule, and Warsele villages in Ngala LGA, killing 11 insurgents. Remaining fatalities recorded in other events.
Armed men kill three men at a hostel in KwaMashu. The motive was unknown
Two men on Kassub camp were killed by government backed militia.
